---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service - Side Badger">
  <section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-header fade-up">
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-muted">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content glass fade-up">
        <div class="placeholder-notice">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/>
            <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/>
            <line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/>
            <polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/>
          </svg>
          <h2>Terms of Service Coming Soon</h2>
          <p>The actual terms of service content will be loaded from the Side Badger API.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">In the meantime, here's the spirit of our terms:</p>
        </div>

        <div class="quick-summary">
          <h3>The Badger's Terms (Plain English Edition)</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Be cool.</strong> Don't use Side Badger to do illegal stuff.</li>
            <li><strong>It's free.</strong> We're not going to charge you, now or ever.</li>
            <li><strong>It's a demo.</strong> Side Badger is a white-label demonstration. It works great, but don't run your Fortune 500 company's expenses through it.</li>
            <li><strong>No warranties.</strong> We built this with love and coffee, but stuff happens. Use at your own risk.</li>
            <li><strong>Your data is yours.</strong> What you put in, you can take out.</li>
            <li><strong>Don't be a jerk.</strong> This covers most edge cases.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="api-placeholder">
          <code>// Terms of service content will be fetched from:</code>
          <code>// GET app.sidebadger.com/api/legal/terms</code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: var(--space-4xl) 0;
    min-height: 70vh;
  }

  .legal-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .placeholder-notice {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .placeholder-notice svg {
    color: var(--accent-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .placeholder-notice h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .placeholder-notice p {
    max-width: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .quick-summary {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .quick-summary h3 {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .quick-summary ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .quick-summary li {
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    position: relative;
  }

  .quick-summary li::before {
    content: 'â†’';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .api-placeholder {
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .api-placeholder code {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
</style>
